    "### Observations\n",
    "\n",
    "What the charts are saying:\n",
    "I’m using the 20 and 50 EMAs to figure out the overall trend. When the gap between them widens, it tells me the trend is real and gaining strength. The MACD underneath is basically my sanity check—it flags whether a price move is actually building steam or secretly running out of gas.\n",
    "\n",
    "To time actual entries, I look at the 14-day RSI alongside volume. A breakout doesn't mean much to me unless volume is spiking above its 20-day average to prove big players are involved. Checking that with the RSI boundaries makes it easy to see when a stock is getting too overextended to buy, or when a sell-off is finally hitting a bottom.\n",
    "\n",
    "What the fundamentals add:\n",
    "The fundamental data is there to make sure the chart isn't lying to us. Comparing the P/E against the PEG ratio tells me instantly if the stock's expensive price tag is actually backed up by real earnings growth. Finally, glancing at the debt and liquidity metrics gives me peace of mind that the company is financially stable and isn't running on fumes."
   ]
  },
